Great Britain remains an important trading partner of Poland, mainly due to the large percentage of Poles living in the UK. The advantage of the British market is primarily its absorption. Unfortunately, due to Brexit, trade in goods has been significantly hampered and shipments of goods are more expensive. All this leads to the slow isolation of the British market from the economies of the European Union. It is also a highly competitive market. (t≈Çumacz angielski https://skrivanek.pl/tlumacz-angielsko-polski-dla-firm/).
